Two different phases, characterized by two distinct exponential growth rates, can be appreciated in Italy (especially when data are plotted in logarithmic scale) by observing the ILI incidence as reported by the surveillance system during the 2009 H1N1 pandemic (see green points in Fig. 4a and its subpanel).
